# ── line endings ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Normalize text to LF in the repo; shell scripts MUST stay LF on checkout
# (a CRLF .sh breaks MSYS bash on the Windows release job and Windows
# clones with autocrlf).  Binary assets are marked so autocrlf never
# touches them.
* text=auto
*.sh text eol=lf
scripts/hooks/* text eol=lf
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.icns binary
*.ttf binary

# ── public-export exclusions ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Paths excluded from any public export (`git archive` / mirror publish):
# internal docs, the project-local agent config, and the private-origin
# CI workflows (inert on GitHub, but noise + infra disclosure) — none
# ship in a public release.
docs/internal/ export-ignore
docs/internal/** export-ignore
CLAUDE.md export-ignore
.gitea/ export-ignore
.gitea/** export-ignore
